a:["$","div",null,{"className":"article-enter-delay-2","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"glass-card overflow-hidden mb-8 !hover:transform-none","children":["$","img",null,{"src":"/images/articles/metas-new-ai-division-engineering-push-or-just-res/main.jpg","alt":"Meta’s new AI division: Engineering push or just reshuffling?","className":"w-full h-auto max-h-[400px] object-cover"}]}]}]
b:["$","div",null,{"className":"article-enter-delay-3 article-prose max-w-none","children":[["$","p",null,{"children":["Meta isn’t just ",["$","em",null,{"children":"talking"}]," about AI anymore—it’s restructuring for it. An internal memo obtained by the ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.wsj.com","children":"Wall Street Journal"}]," reveals the company is consolidating its applied AI efforts into a dedicated engineering division, a move that signals a shift from research-heavy projects like Llama to shipping tangible product improvements. The timing isn’t accidental: with ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://blog.google/technology/ai/google-search-generative-ai/","children":"Google’s AI-overhauled Search"}]," and ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://blogs.microsoft.com/blog/2024/05/20/introducing-copilot-pcs/","children":"Microsoft’s Copilot+ PCs"}]," dominating headlines, Meta’s quiet reorganization reads like a bid to turn its AI lab’s promise into user-facing reality."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["The new division, according to available information, will focus on embedding AI deeper into Meta’s core products—think smarter ad targeting in Instagram, more responsive chatbots in WhatsApp, or perhaps even ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://ai.meta.com/blog/meta-ai-assistant/","children":"AI agents that automate tasks"}]," across its apps. But here’s the catch: Meta already has AI teams. The question isn’t whether this division exists, but whether it can cut through the company’s notorious silos. Early signals suggest the goal is to streamline deployment, reducing the lag between a model’s training and its appearance in, say, your Facebook feed. For developers, this could mean clearer APIs and fewer hoops to jump through when integrating Meta’s AI tools."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["Yet the industry has seen this movie before. ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.theverge.com/2023/4/20/23693392/google-ai-reorganization-deepmind-brain-research-labs","children":"Google’s repeated AI reorgs"}]," and ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.businessinsider.com/amazon-alexa-layoffs-ai-strategy-shift-2023-11","children":"Amazon’s fragmented Alexa teams"}]," prove that new divisions don’t automatically equal better products. Meta’s advantage? Its AI research—like the open-source ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://ai.meta.com/blog/meta-llama-3/","children":"Llama 3"}],"—already has traction with developers. The risk? That this becomes another layer of management between the lab and the user, slowing things down further."]}],"\n",["$","p",null,{"children":["The practical impact hinges on execution. If the division succeeds, businesses using Meta’s ads platform might see more precise audience tools, while creators could get AI-assisted editing features in Reels. But if it stumbles, we’ll get another round of ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.theverge.com/2023/9/27/23893762/meta-ai-assistants-chatbots-whatsapp-instagram-messenger","children":"‘Meta’s AI is coming soon’"}]," headlines with little to show for it. The tech press is watching closely—not for the announcement, but for the first sign of actual change in how Meta’s 3 billion users interact with its apps."]}],"\n",["$","div",null,{"className":"not-prose my-8 pt-6 border-t border-white/10","children":[null,["$","div",null,{"className":"glass-card overflow-hidden mb-4 !hover:transform-none","children":["$","img",null,{"src":"/images/articles/metas-new-ai-division-engineering-push-or-just-res/subtitle.jpg","alt":"Why a quiet org chart change could mean faster features—or just more bureaucracy","className":"w-full h-auto max-h-[400px] object-cover"}]}],"$L13"]}],"\n","$L14","\n","$L15","\n","$L16","\n","$L17"]}]
