13:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-text-secondary italic text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium","children":"Why a quiet org chart change could mean faster features—or just more bureaucracy"}]
14:["$","p",null,{"children":["For the average user, this reorganization won’t matter—until it does. The real test isn’t whether Meta can build another AI model, but whether it can make ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.theverge.com/2023/9/27/23893468/meta-ray-ban-smart-glasses-ai-assistant-price-release-date","children":"Ray-Ban Meta smart glasses"}]," answer questions faster or Instagram’s Explore tab surface genuinely relevant content. The company’s AI has long been a mixed bag: brilliant at recommending ads, less so at understanding nuanced user queries. A dedicated engineering division could bridge that gap—or it could become another victim of Meta’s ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.wired.com/2014/04/facebook-broken/","children":"‘move fast and break things’"}]," legacy, where speed trumps polish."]}]
15:["$","p",null,{"children":["Market context matters here. Meta isn’t just competing with Google and Microsoft; it’s racing against ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.perplexity.ai/","children":"startups like Perplexity"}]," and ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://inflection.ai/","children":"inflection.ai"}]," that are shipping consumer-facing AI tools with far less bureaucracy. The pressure is on to prove that Meta’s scale—its data, its user base, its infrastructure—can outpace nimbler rivals. If this division accelerates features like ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://ai.meta.com/blog/emimic-gen-ai-image-editing/","children":"AI-generated image editing"}]," or real-time translation in Messenger, it could redefine how millions interact with social media. If it doesn’t, Meta risks ceding ground to platforms where AI feels less like a demo and more like a utility."]}]
16:["$","p",null,{"children":["What’s missing from the memo? Any mention of ",["$","em",null,{"children":"how"}]," this division will collaborate with Meta’s existing AI research teams or its ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://ai.meta.com/research/","children":"FAIR lab"}],". Without tight integration, we’re looking at another silo—one that might prioritize shipping over innovation. The developer community, already ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://techcrunch.com/2023/07/12/meta-shuts-down-its-november-2022-launched-ai-language-model-galactica/","children":"frustrated by Meta’s shifting APIs"}],", will be watching for concrete improvements: better documentation, more stable SDKs, or actual access to the models powering these features."]}]
17:["$","p",null,{"children":["The most telling detail? This news didn’t come from Meta. It leaked. That suggests either a lack of confidence in the rollout or a deliberate strategy to temper expectations. Either way, the subtext is clear: Meta knows it needs to show progress, not just promise. The next six months will reveal whether this division is a turning point—or just another footnote in the company’s long history of ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-03-14/meta-s-latest-reorg-shows-zuckerberg-is-still-searching-for-a-strategy","children":"reorganizing its way to relevance"}],"."]}]
